    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-20T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-20T04:00:00-05:00" n="845"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d845">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/389: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Istanbul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-20T12:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 20, 1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. Department’s 95, August 17. I have today communicated to the Prime Minister
                    substance of Department’s cable under reference.</p>
                <p>In connection with a visit made to Ankara and Istanbul by Jackson, head of the
                    MESC, and Fred Winant,<note n="64" xml:id="d845fn64">American representative on
                        the Middle East Supply Center.</note> I had occasion to discuss with them
                    the delivery of the 15,000 tons of wheat. Jackson stated that he expected to be
                    able to deliver 5,000 tons by September 15 and 5,000 additional tons by October
                    15 but that the delivery to Turkey of the final 5,000 tons would be dependent
                    upon the arrival in the Middle <pb facs="0749" n="737" xml:id="pg_737"/> East of
                    the first of the shipments from the United States sent in replacement of the
                    10,000 tons already advanced by the MESC.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
